The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, January 05, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, January 5, 2004				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	All roads off Red Road from 5 am to 9 am for Republic Day parade practice.				 																Animal tales				 																																	The Beastly Beatitudes film festival presents The Company of Wolves, Neil Jordans take on Little Red Riding Hood, Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, at 6 pm.				 																Film fest				 																																	Fictional Truths  Beyond Festival, a session of alternative cinema, presented by the Eisenstein Cine Club amp; Drik India, to be inaugurated by Mrinal Sen, at Gorky Sadan, 6 pm. Vaseeyat by Rajiv Kumar and Drishyantar by Joshy Joseph to be screened.				 																Music				 																																	Usha Uthup and Chandrabindoo members Anindya and Upal to launch Annyo Goppo, the debut album of Bangla band Roopkatha by Sony Music, at Music World, 2 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	Small wonders, an exhibition of works by Paritosh Sen, Rabin Mondal, Prakash Karmakar and Sanat Kar, at Vikalp Art Shop, Swabhumi, 2 pm to 8 pm.				 																																	The Homecoming  A Winter Symphony, an exhibition of Indian art and sculpture featuring works of artists like Ramananda Bandopadhyay and Ganesh Haloi, at Idiyas Gallery, 10.30 am to 7.30 pm.				 																																	A display of paintings by Kalyani Roy at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, from 3 pm to 8 pm.				 																Fair				 																																	The closing day of the 10th Vidyasagar Mela on the Maidan.
